Package com.cafean.client.ic

Class AbstractConditionSetManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.client.ic.AbstractConditionSetManager
  • public abstract class AbstractConditionSetManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This is the abstract parent to the condition set managers for the different plug-in. This allows for custom handling of the condition sets through for individual plug-ins.

        Parameters:
        name - The unique name for the condition set.
        Returns:
        the ConditionSet with the matching name or NULL if no such set exists.

      • ImportConditionSet

        public static ConditionSet ImportConditionSet​(AbstractNumericsModel model,
                                              java.lang.String name,
                                              java.nio.file.Path file)
        This method imports a condition set into the current model. This does not add the new condition set to the provided model, so that this method can be used by the condition set dialog.
        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractNumericsModel on which the condition set will apply
        name - the new name for the condition set.
        file - the Path to the file to import
        Returns:
        the ConditionSet imported from the file.

      • importAndAddConditionSet

        public ConditionSet importAndAddConditionSet​(java.lang.String setName,
                                             java.lang.String fileName)
        This method imports a new condition set from the provided file name. If the file name is not absolute it is assumed to be relative to the current models save file, unless the current model has not been saved.
        Parameters:
        setName - the unique name for the ConditionSet. If this corresponds to an existing set, the existing set will be replaced with the contents of the file.
        fileName - the file location that will be imported.
        Returns:
        the ConditionSet created by the import.
        See Also:
        importAndAddConditionSet(java.lang.String, java.nio.file.Path)

      • importAndAddConditionSet

        public ConditionSet importAndAddConditionSet​(java.lang.String name,
                                             java.nio.file.Path file)
        This method imports a new condition set from the provided file location. The file must be in CSV format where the first column contains the unique property keys and the second column contains the value for each location. The # character as the first character on a line will be treated as a comment character.
        Parameters:
        name - the unique name for the ConditionSet. If this corresponds to an existing set, the existing set will be replaced with the contents of the file.
        file - the Path to the file location that will be imported.
        Returns:
        the ConditionSet created by the import.

      • exportConditionSet

        public static void exportConditionSet​(AbstractNumericsModel model,
                                      ConditionSet set,
                                      java.nio.file.Path path,
                                      boolean includeMetaData)
        This method generates an condition set file that contains the data in the condition set in the sets current units.
        Parameters:
        model - the AbstractNumericsModel that is being modified.
        set - the ConditionSet that will be exported.
        path - the Path to the target exported file
        includeMetaData - a boolean flag that allows suppressing the meta data at the top of the file.

      • applyConditionSet

        public void applyConditionSet​(java.awt.Window parent,
                              ChannelDataHolder set,
                              boolean preserveNumerics)
        Applies a ChannelDataHolder object to the model. If the current object is a PartialConditionSet, this will only apply the condition set to the components referenced in that set.
        Parameters:
        parent - the Window parent for the operation so a progress monitor can be instantiated.
        set - the ChannelDataHolder that will be applied to the current model
        preserveNumerics - the flag that indicates whether references to numeric variables should be preserved.

      • storeInConditionSet

        public void storeInConditionSet​(java.awt.Window parent,
                                ConditionSet original)
        This method stores the current model initial condition sets in the provided ConditionSet object. If the condition set is a PartialConditionSet this will only add conditions from components selected in that PartialConditionSet.
        Parameters:
        parent - the Window parent GUI object for the ProgressMon.
        original - the ConditionSet that will be updated with the initial conditions.

      • addComponent

        public void addComponent​(ConditionSet set,
                         AbstractComponent comp)
        This method adds a single component to a condition set. This only modifies the condition set if it extends PartialConditionSet. This adds the component to the list of selected components, and updates the condition set to include the current initial conditions.
        Parameters:
        set - the ConditionSet to be updated.
        comp - the AbstractComponent to be added to the condition set.

      • removeComponent

        public void removeComponent​(ConditionSet set,
                            AbstractComponent comp)
        This method removes a single component to a condition set. This only modifies the condition set if it extends PartialConditionSet. This removes the component from the list of selected components, and updates the condition set to exclude the initial condition values.
        Parameters:
        set - the ConditionSet to be updated.
        comp - the AbstractComponent to be removed from the condition set.
